# PostgREST: constrained queries & pagination

## Objective

Prevent **full table scans** via PostgREST (`select` without meaningful filters) because they:

- harm performance/server **LCP**,
- hit practical limits (~1000 rows / payloads),
- block scaling later.

Any **business list** touching hundreds+ rows must bootstrap as **server-paginated** (or aggregated RPC/count+range combos), never ‚Äúpull everything ‚Üí filter server-side arbitrarily‚Äù nor ‚Äúsprinkle `.limit()` and forget paging‚Äù.

## Rules (mandatory on new code)

1. Avoid `from("‚Ä¶").select("*")` **without** tight filters (`eq`, scoped `in`, date windows, FK-bounded lookups, ‚Ä¶) except intentional exceptions cited below.
2. Avoid querying large domain tables (`profiles`, `registrations`, `payments`, `user_events`, `section_enrollments`, ‚Ä¶) without at least **one** guardrail among: restrictive predicates, deterministic ordering + **`range`** windows, **`head:true` counting alone**, or a **purpose-built RPC** sized for throughput.
3. Prefer **explicit column lists** (`select("id, name, status")`) versus `*` to reduce payloads and surprise deltas under RLS/migrations.
4. **Admin/list UIs**: **mandatory server pagination** when growth is unbounded:
   - Rows via **`range`**, totals via **`count: "exact", head:true` in parallel‚Äîor RPC exposing `{ rows, total }`.
   - Sorting/filter predicates live **inside** queries/RPC‚Äînot only ‚Äúwhatever rows happened to arrive‚Äù on the client.
   - Forbidden: lone `.limit(N)` on limitless listings **without navigation + authoritative totals**.
5. Anti-pattern‚Äî‚Äú**client pagination only**‚Äù: loading **all rows** inside an RSC then slicing in hooks still performs a **scan** upstream. Pagination must reside **ahead** of the client boundary (`searchParams`/actions handing page+total tuples).
6. **Bounded ID lists**: `.in("id", ids)` is safe **only when** IDs have credible business ceilings. If unconstrained growth is possible, **paginate origins** or **chunk** `.in()` calls (~200 UUID batches) avoiding URL/request blowups.
7. **Charts / aggregates / histograms**: favor **RPC SQL aggregates** versus `select id,role` over entire populations. New admin RPC warrants **`10`** (mini PR note/ADR).

## Canonical patterns already in-repo (reuse before reinventing)

| Scenario | Implementation reference |
|------|-------------|
| Admin registrations + filters + paging | `src/lib/dashboard/loadPaginatedRegistrations.ts`, `src/app/[locale]/dashboard/admin/registrations/page.tsx`, `useAdminRegistrationsList` |
| Paginated profiles + masked emails/page | `src/lib/dashboard/loadPaginatedAdminUsers.ts`, `users` page hook `useAdminUsersTable` |
| Chunk `.in(...)` explosions | `src/lib/supabase/chunkedIn.ts` |
| Admin hub aggregates w/o scans | RPC `admin_hub_profile_counts`, migration `031_admin_hub_profile_counts_rpc.sql`, loader `src/lib/dashboard/loadAdminHubSummary.ts` |
| **Dashboard filter aggregates** across roles | RPC + loaders ‚Äî **`24-dashboard-list-filter-aggregates-rpc.mdc`** (`admin_users_list_role_counts`, `112_*`, loader `loadAdminUsersListRoleCounts.ts`) |
| Cron ingestion at scale | sane batch `limit`, stable ordering + idempotent resumes (see `src/app/api/cron/churn-inactivity/route.ts`) |
| `UniversalListView`/`TablePagination` | pagination totals derive from **matching server aggregates**, never `pageRows.length`. |

## Documentable exceptions

- Tiny **configuration catalogs** anchored at &lt;100 rows documented as fixed.
- **Migrations/seeds/scripts** under `supabase/migrations/` or `scripts/` (ops only).
- **count-only queries** (`head:true`, bounded filters).
- **PK lookups** (`.eq("id", uuid).maybeSingle()`).
- **Safety caps on proven small catalogs** (e.g. institute sections)‚ÄîPR must cite ceiling & UX fallback if hit.

